div.p:
"Was there no Canada?" said Mrs. North, biting off her thread. "O, I recollect;
                  Hagar went there. I wonder if the angel who remanded her was removed from office,
                  on his return to heaven."

q.p:
"But, it is said, the slave is too much exposed to the master's abuse of power;
                     he is liable to wrongs without a remedy; and, so far, his condition is below
                     that of the hired laborer.
